      "content": "i hear you about public safety, but when you say \"prioritizing the safety\" of society, isn't that just a way of saying that constitutional rights are less important than what the government thinks is safe? it feels like you're dismissing the whole legal/constitutional argument as something that just needs to be \"balanced\" away. isn't it true that for many people, those rights aren't up for negotiation or \"balancing\" at all?",
